<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1886-07-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1886-07-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="331" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d331">
                    <head>No. 327.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Jackson</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1886-07-29"><hi rend="italic">July</hi> 29,
                            1886</date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p>Consul at Piedras Negras reports Francisco Arresures, naturalized American,
                        extradited, notwithstanding his citizenship, by Texan magistrates.</p>
                    <p>Return demanded by consul, but denied. Arresures taken from jail and shot by
                        Mexican authorities.</p>
                    <p>Ask prompt investigation of this alleged murder and punishment of criminals,
                        reserving all questions under treaty of extradition.</p>
                    <closer><signed>BAYARD.</signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>